Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna A member of the House of Representatives, representing Jema’a/Sanga Federal constituency of Kaduna State, Shehu Garba, has appointed 79 aides to assist him in discharging his responsibilities. Garba’s Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mock Kure, made this known via a statement released to newsmen in Kaduna on Monday. The lawmaker, who is also the House Committee Chairman on Anti-Corruption, congratulated his constituents on the 21 years of unbroken democracy in the country. Garba stressed the need for unity and peaceful coexistence among Nigerians irrespective of their political, religious and ethnic affinities for the growth of democracy in the country. The statement said the 79 aides were chosen from the 23 wards that make up the Jema’a/Sanga Federal Constituency. Garba was quoted as saying, “These aides were chosen on the basis of their competence, deep commitment to the PDP and grass-roots orientation and are expected to contribute in bringing representation closer to the people. “These appointments will help in empowering and motivating party faithfuls and also contribute to the sustenance, and visibility of the party in the Constituency.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 